18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
19 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 1, Chapter 24, O.S.L. 2022
20 (70 O.S. Supp. 2024, Section 3231), is amended to read as follows:
21 Section 3231. A. This act shall be known and may be cited as
22 the “Oklahoma National Guard Educational Assistance Act”.
23 B. As used in this act the Oklahoma National Guard Educational
24 Assistance Act:
ENGR. S. B. NO. 32 Page 1

1 1. “Oklahoma educational institution” means an institution of
2 higher education within The Oklahoma State System of Higher
3 Education;
4 2. “Eligible Guard member” means a current member of the
5 Oklahoma National Guard in good standing who has a high school
6 diploma or who has completed General Educational Development (GED)
7 requirements and who has secured admission to and enrolled in an
8 Oklahoma educational institution;
9 3. “Graduate program” means a program offered by an Oklahoma
10 educational institution that leads to the award of a master’s
11 degree;
12 4. “Program” means the Oklahoma National Guard Educational
13 Assistance Program established pursuant to the provisions of this
14 section; and
15 5. “Undergraduate program” means a program offered by an
16 Oklahoma educational institution that leads to the award of an
17 associate’s degree or a baccalaureate degree.
18 C. There is hereby created the Oklahoma National Guard
19 Educational Assistance Program to provide assistance to eligible
20 Guard members who enroll in an Oklahoma educational institution.
21 Subject to the availability of funds and limitations established by
22 the Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education, the amount of
23 assistance shall be equivalent to the amount of resident tuition,
24 mandatory fees, and program fees, academic service fees, and any
ENGR. S. B. NO. 32 Page 2

1 othe r fees for courses in which the eligible Guard member is
2 enrolled, not to exceed a maximum of eighteen (18) credit hours each
3 semester. The mandatory fees, program fees, academic service fees,
4 and any other fees for courses shall be jointly reviewed by the
5 State Regents and the Military Department of the State of Oklahoma.
6 The State Regents may determine fees or fee amounts to be ineligible
7 for program assistance. If the State Regents make such a
8 determination, program assistance for those fees or fee amounts
9 shall not be provided to eligible Guard members participating in the
10 program.
11 1. The amount of assistance provided to an eligible Guard
12 member enrolled in an undergraduate program shall not exceed a
13 maximum of one hundred twenty (120) credit hours in pursuit of an
14 associate’s degree and/or a baccalaureate degree.
15 2. Subject to the assistance for eligible Guard members
16 enrolled in undergraduate programs being fully funded, assistance
17 shall be provided to an eligible Guard member with a baccalaureate
18 degree enrolled in a graduate program. The amount of assistance
19 provided to an eligible Guard member enrolled in a graduate program
20 shall not exceed a maximum of forty (40) credit hours in pursuit of
21 a master’s degree.
22 3. Assistance provided pursuant to this section shall be
23 granted without any limitation other than the amount of funds
24 available for the Program program and the number of eligible Guard
ENGR. S. B. NO. 32 Page 3

1 memb ers who apply, subject to any cap established by the Military
2 Department.
3 4. Assistance allowed by this section shall not be allowed for
4 courses taken in excess of the requirements for completion of an
5 undergraduate program or a graduate program, whichever is applicable
6 for the eligible Guard member.
7 D. Assistance provided pursuant to this section shall be
8 allocated to the Oklahoma educational institution from the Oklahoma
9 National Guard Educational Assistance Revolving Fund created
10 pursuant to Section 2 3232 of this act title.
11 E. To be eligible to apply for the Program program, an eligible
12 Guard member shall:
13 1. Have at least one (1) year remaining on his or her
14 enlistment contract at the beginning of any semester for which the
15 member applies for assistance pursuant to this section;
16 2. Agree in writing to complete his or her current service
17 obligation in the Oklahoma National Guard; and
18 3. Agree in writing to serve actively in good standing with the
19 Oklahoma National Guard for not less than twenty-four (24) months
20 after completion of the last semester for which the member receives
21 assistance pursuant to this section.
22 F. To retain eligibility for the Program program, an eligible
23 Guard member shall:
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 32 Page 4

1 1. Maintain good academic standing and satisfactory academic
2 progress according to standards of the Oklahoma educational
3 institution in which the member is enrolled;
4 2. Maintain the requirements for retention and degree
5 completion as established by the Oklahoma educational institution in
6 which the member is enrolled;
7 3. Maintain a minimum grade point average of 2.0 on a 4.0
8 scale; and
9 4. Maintain satisfactory participation in the Oklahoma National
10 Guard; and
11 5. Possess a Military Occupational Specialty (MOS) or Air Force
12 Specialty Code (AFSC) after his or her first semester.
13 G. An eligible Guard member seeking assistance pursuant to the
14 provisions of this section shall submit an application on a form
15 prescribed by the Military Department of the State of Oklahoma to
16 the Educational Service Office of the Military Department prior to
17 the semester for which assistance is sought. The eligible Guard
18 member’s Commander or his or her designee shall confirm a member’s
19 standing and eligibility to the Oklahoma educational institution in
20 which the student is enrolled. The Military Department may
21 establish a cap on the number of eligible Guard members allowed to
22 participate per semester per undergraduate or graduate program.
23 H. The eligible Guard member’s Commander may deny an
24 application submitted by an eligible Guard member for continued
ENGR. S. B. NO. 32 Page 5

1 Prog ram program assistance if he or she fails to comply with the
2 provisions of paragraph 1, 2, or 3, 4, or 5 of subsection F of this
3 section.
4 I. An eligible Guard member who has received Program program
5 assistance pursuant to the provisions of this section and who fails
6 to comply with the provisions of paragraph 4 of subsection F of this
7 section shall be required to repay an amount to be calculated as
8 follows:
9 1. Determine the total amount of assistance provided pursuant
10 to the provisions of this section;
11 2. Divide the amount determined in paragraph 1 of this
12 subsection by twenty-four (24); and
13 3. Multiply the amount determined in paragraph 2 of this
14 subsection by the number of months the member did not fulfill the
15 requirements of paragraph 4 of subsection F of this section.
16 Repayments shall be deposited into the Oklahoma National Guard
17 Educational Assistance Revolving Fund created pursuant to Section 2
18 3232 of this act title.
19 J. An eligible Guard member who has received Program program
20 assistance pursuant to the provisions of this section and who fails
21 to comply with the provisions of paragraph 4 of subsection F of this
22 section due to hardship circumstances may request a waiver from
23 repayment. A waiver request shall be submitted in writing to the
24 Adjutant General.
